        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Three profiles dominate: families who want the Graceville or Chelmer lifestyle at a more accessible entry point; buyers who have been searching the inner south-west corridor and have found Sherwood represents relative value while still being close to the Oxley Creek green space and the Sherwood Arboretum; and investors looking at the long-term trajectory of the south-west river corridor as infrastructure and amenity improvements drive capital growth.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell in Sherwood?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-presented Sherwood homes at accurate prices typically sell in 30 to 45 days. The active buyer pool benefits from Chelmer and Graceville overflow, which adds meaningful competition for correctly positioned stock. Properties with clear Oxley Creek or arboretum aspects and good character credentials tend to generate stronger competition at auction.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What drives value in Sherwood?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Proximity to Chelmer and Graceville, and buyers' perception of Sherwood as the accessible entry into the inner south-west corridor, is the primary value driver. Secondary drivers include proximity to Sherwood Arboretum, character home integrity (original Queenslanders and well-maintained post-war homes), block size, and Sherwood train station access.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#1c1917; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How does Sherwood compare to Chelmer and Graceville?
          <span style="color:#c4912a; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Sherwood shares the inner south-west river corridor character with Chelmer and Graceville but typically offers a more accessible entry price. Buyers who have been searching Chelmer and Graceville and found themselves outcompeted often redirect to Sherwood, which adds a consistent overflow buyer pool. Sherwood's own character home stock and the Oxley Creek and arboretum green space give it a genuine independent identity rather than just a consolation option.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

